title: My video blog
description:
Just, you know, some bits from my life.

When I made the decision to move overseas I wanted a way to keep my friends back home updated, but also kinda a keepsake for myself. Also I really enjoy making new videos, so here we are! 

Hope you enjoy!

videos.title: Lisbon: Day trip to Belem Tower (and why I need a new tripod)
videos.description:
Visiting Portugal in winter means a high chance of getting rained out. After a big night out, I schlep (hung over) to Belem to visit the historic tower, and get blown away by the sudden onset of a rainstorm. Featuring some high quality knowledge insights for your viewing pleasure, and a surprise cameo from the wonderful Corina with well wishes from Amsterdam.

videos.title: A quick stroll around the Amsterdam Light Festival
videos.description:
When they erected a giant lamp outside my work I thought it was a christmas decoration. Turns out it was one of thirty installations for the seventh edition of the Amsterdam Light Festival.

https://amsterdamlightfestival.com/en/

Super annoyed at myself for running around two nights in a row with image stabilization turned off, it makes a HUGE difference compared to fixing it in post.

videos.title: Windblocker - a thing to do video in the wind
videos.description:
This place is pretty windy, and a few of my videos have been plagued with crappy sound. So I bought a "Windblocker" (google it), which clips onto the phone and acts like a dead cat windscreen for the built in phone mic.

It's not 100% perfect, but it's definitely way better than a stock phone mic. I'm sold.
